
1. How to move to beginning and end of the statement in command line/bash:

To move to beginning of the statement/line use 'ctrl+a' which takes the cursor to the beginning of the line/statement.
To move to end of the line/statement use 'ctrl+e' which takes the cursor to the end of the statement.

2. How to move forward and backward one work at a time in a statement or line in bash?

To move cursor one word forward in a statement use 'alt+f' and 'alt+b' for backward moment of cursor.

3. How to delete preceding word in bash?

To delete preceding word in bash use 'alt+backspace'.

4. How to delete following word in bash?

To delete following word where cursor placed in bash use 'alt+d'.